hopobject.body: Do you need a work permit? http //farma-sport.com "The funny thing is often in these situations, when it's raining and it's crazy or it's super hot, often the crowd is more responsive to you because they kind of need to get into it more to forget the sh---y conditions," Grobler tells U.S. News after his set. "People who don't really care about music won't make the effort to come out as much as the people who just really want to be there for the music."
